    "name": "committed_2016_mid_econ",
    "description": "Maps the committed_split threshold in the 2016-block retarget regime at moderate economic support (econ=0.55). Companion to committed_2016_high_econ.\nRESEARCH QUESTION: Does lower economic support shift the committed_split threshold in the 2016-block regime? At econ=0.55 vs econ=0.78, the initial price gap is smaller (~4.4% vs ~12.8% v27 premium). Smaller initial gap means neutral pools drift more slowly toward v27, potentially requiring more committed v27 hashrate to reach 2016 blocks before v26 retargets.\nPRIOR CONTEXT: - econ=0.55 confirmed v27_dominant at committed_split=0.35 in econ_threshold_2016_v2 - econ=0.55 maps to 1 economic node on v27 (56.7% custody, same as 0.35\u20130.70) - Cascade timing at econ=0.55 (1 node, baseline): similar to \u22488426s as at econ=0.78 - The economic support level affects NEUTRAL pool drift speed, not committed pools\nPRICE GAP AT START (econ contribution only):\n  econ_f_v27 = 0.8 + 0.55*0.4 = 1.02; econ_f_v26 = 0.8 + 0.45*0.4 = 0.98\n  Initial gap \u2248 4% (small, neutral pools drift slowly)\nvs econ=0.78:\n  gap \u2248 12.8% (large, neutral pools drift quickly to v27)\n\nCOMMITTED_SPLIT INTERPRETATION:\n  committed_split=0.20: v27=14%, v26=56%, neutral=30%\n  committed_split=0.30: v27=21%, v26=49%, neutral=30%\n  committed_split=0.40: v27=28%, v26=42%, neutral=30%\n  committed_split=0.50: v27=35%, v26=35%, neutral=30%  (symmetric)\n\nRun command:\n  python tools/sweep/3_run_sweep.py \\\n    --input tools/sweep/committed_2016_mid_econ/build_manifest.json \\\n    --namespace sweep-com2016-mid \\\n    --results-dir committed_2016_mid_econ/results \\\n    --duration 13000 --retarget-interval 2016 --interval 2\n\nNamespace to create first:\n  kubectl create namespace sweep-com2016-mid\n\nWall-clock: 4 scenarios \u00d7 13,000s = 52,000s \u2248 14.4h\n",
